# RC Low-Pass Filter
# ===================
# A simple first-order RC low-pass filter.
# This is a purely linear circuit - no nonlinear components.
#
# Cutoff frequency: fc = 1 / (2 * pi * R * C)
# With R = 10k and C = 10n: fc â‰ˆ 1.59 kHz
#
# This is useful as a tone control or high-frequency roll-off.

# Input voltage source - driven by audio samples
V_IN    in      0       AC

# Input resistor
R1      in      out     10k

# Filter capacitor to ground
C1      out     0       10n

# Define input and output nodes
.input  in
.output out
